--- abstract

High reliability and low jitter can be achieved by being able to send data packets through multiple paths, via different parents, in a network. This document details how to exchange the necessary information within RPL control packets to let a node better select the different parents that will be used to forward a packet over different paths. This document also describes how to apply Common Ancestor policies to implement multi-path routing.

